-- Lifan Industry Plans to Raise $222 Million in Shanghai Initial Offering
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-11T23:07:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/lifan-industry-plans-to-raise-222-million-in-shanghai-initial-offering.html
Lifan Industry (Group) Co. plans to
raise 1.48 billion yuan in an initial public offering in
Shanghai, according to a statement from the company on the China
Securities Regulatory Commission website.  The Chongqing-based Chinese automaker will sell as many as
200 million shares, the statement said.  The commission said in a separate statement it will review
the listing on Oct. 15.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 gturk2@bloomberg.net  